                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/409: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Luxemburg</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Waller</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-28T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 28, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Your 16, June 27, noon. Invitations to attend the Evian meeting were extended
                    only to those countries which offered some reasonable possibility of accepting a
                    substantial number of immigrants. Inasmuch as Luxemburg can not be considered in
                    that category we consider it impracticable to extend an invitation, at least at
                    the present stage of proceedings.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
